## Status definitions

Each repository is classified into exactly one of the following statuses:

- **active** — Pushed within the last 12 months and not archived. Eligible for compliance workflow onboarding.
- **stale** — No commits in the last 12 months and not archived. Triage decision needed: archive, revive, or keep as historical. See "Archive candidates" for triage hints.
- **archived** — Repository marked as archived on GitHub. Read-only; excluded from active compliance programs. See the Open Source Policy for handling of historical findings.

The "Likely owner" column uses these suffixes:

- **(CO)** — Owner derived from the repository's CODEOWNERS file. Authoritative.
- **(committer)** — Owner derived from the dominant author in the last 100 commits. May be historical if the repo is stale.
- **(unowned)** — No CODEOWNERS file and no non-bot commits found in the last 200 commits.
